        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu,browser,msteams,azure-speech,bedrock-mantle,googlechat,huggingface,perplexity): bound JSON response reads",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nReplace unbounded `await response.json()` with `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB cap)\nacross 8 channel/provider modules (15 call sites in 15 files).\n\n## Changes\n\nModules: feishu, browser, msteams, azure-speech, bedrock-mantle, googlechat,\nhuggingface, perplexity. Each site uses a file-local constant.\n\nAlso fixed 15 missing constant definitions and 2 missing imports.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Untrusted API responses must not be buffered whole;\n  the read must stop at the 1 MiB cap, cancel the stream, and throw a bounded\n  error — while valid small responses still parse unchanged.\n- **Real environment tested**: A real `node:http` server streaming\n  Content-Length-less JSON bodies. Real `fetch()`, real TCP socket, real\n  `readResponseWithLimit`. Node v22.12.0.\n\n## Evidence\n### Real HTTP proof (against live server)\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_bounded_json.mts\n\n[proof] real server, cap=1048576 bytes, would-stream≈67108864 bytes\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error :: msg=\"Error: JSON response exceeds 1048576 bytes\"\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: server sent ≈ cap bytes, not ~64 MiB :: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly :: status=ok id=batch-1\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap :: buffered=33554457 bytes (> 1048576)\n\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\nThe proof harness starts a real `node:http` server with no Content-Length,\nstreams ~64 MiB of JSON, and verifies `readResponseWithLimit` cancels the\nstream at the 1 MiB cap. The negative control proves the cap is load-bearing.\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/feishu/src/streaming-card.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n       Tests  17 passed (17)\n```\n\n**Label**: security\n\n_AI-assisted._\n",
        "branch": "fix/batch3-bounded-json",
